data.title: Perfect Small town americana
data.text:

data.title: Not what I remembered
data.text: Too bad the quality at he Dairy Delite seems to have dwindled.  Many choices for flavored cones, but, weird after taste.  Hate to say it but DQ has a much better product.  I hope the Dairy Delite takes reviews seriously because it would be sad to see it go under for overpriced and lower quality snacks.

data.title: A Lakeville institution
data.text:
Dairy Delite is a 50s style walk-up ice cream stand in downtown Lakeville. I can't believe there aren't already reviews for it, because it is a Lakeville institution. They are open from April to October, and it's a sad day in the fall when they shut down for the season. All summer long, there are lines of people waiting for their treats. It is a favorite of kids on bikes, baseball and soccer teams, and families looking for something cold on a hot day. They serve ice cream in many ways, including traditional cones, shakes, floats, and sundaes, as well as their version of the blizzard. Their soft serve is as good as, or better than, Dairy Queen, and the prices are lower. Dairy Delite also has burgers, hot dogs, cheese curds, sloppy joes, and the like, which means you can go for an entire meal and not just dessert.

Whenever you go, plan to wait for a bit. As mentioned before, the place is popular, and the service isn't super fast. The employees are working hard, but it takes a while to crank out all of their orders. Have a seat and be patient. The kids can play on the playground.

Stop by and see what everyone on Lakeville knows-- Dairy Delite is the best place for ice cream around.
